column3: The first IV and DV (in the coding sheet) are the primary IV and DV of the 2nd experiment (in the Abstract) and the Second IV and DV (in this coding sheet) are the primary IV and FDV of the third experiment (in the abstract)… to save arguments I have put the first IV and DV as 'the primary IV/DV tested in the research article' and the second IV/DV as 'the secondary IV/DV tested in the research article

Second study (in journal) Weekly Leisure Activity Score was only collected for 76 participants and reflectance spectra was only obtained for 37 and supplementation aspect of the study, 10 participants completed 8 weeks of β-carotene supplementation. Also… not all of the participants completed all aspects of the third study...
The guardian had millions of quotes but I only coded the first four which were all quotes from the author that were not in the press release…
